function keep_only_names(words)
    return filter(w -> isuppercase(w[1]), words)
end
```

This function `keep_only_names` takes a list of words `words` as input. It uses the `filter` function to create a new list containing only the words that start with an uppercase letter. The anonymous function `w -> isuppercase(w[1])` is used as the filter condition, where `w[1]` returns the first character of the word `w`, and `isuppercase` checks if that character is an uppercase letter. The `filter` function applies this condition to each word in the input `words` list and returns a new list containing only the words that satisfy the condition.
